readcrumbs":["Documentation","Build"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli"},"208":{"id":"cli-0","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli","content":"Every shade CLI command and flag: keygen, address, send, scan, balance, claim and withdraw, plus secret handling and the encrypted keystore format."},"209":{"id":"cli-1","page_id":"cli","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"Conventions"},"210":{"id":"cli-2","page_id":"cli","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`shade keygen`"},"211":{"id":"cli-3","page_id":"cli","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli#shade-address","content":"`shade address`"},"212":{"id":"cli-4","page_id":"cli","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli#shade-send","content":"`shade send`"},"213":{"id":"cli-5","page_id":"cli","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli#shade-scan","content":"`shade scan`"},"214":{"id":"cli-6","page_id":"cli","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli#shade-balance","content":"`shade balance`"},"215":{"id":"cli-7","page_id":"cli","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli#shade-claim","content":"`shade claim`"},"216":{"id":"cli-8","page_id":"cli","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli#shade-withdraw","content":"`shade withdraw`"},"217":{"id":"cli-9","page_id":"cli","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli#local-state","content":"Local state"},"218":{"id":"cli-10","page_id":"cli","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/cli#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"219":{"id":"cli-11","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli","content":"\\{/\\* adapted from shade\\@36217c4 docs/06-cli-reference.md \\*/}"},"220":{"id":"cli-12","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli","content":"import \\{ Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout';"},"221":{"id":"cli-13","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli","content":"`shade` is the reference command-line tool and the fastest way to run the whole flow. Install it with `npm install -g stellar-shade`. Seven commands: `keygen`, `address`, `send`, `scan`, `balance`, `claim`, `withdraw`."},"222":{"id":"cli-14","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"**Secrets.** Every secret resolves in this order: **inline flag, then environment variable, then a non-echoing stderr prompt**. Flags exist for scripting but leak into shell history and `ps` output, so prefer the env var or the prompt."},"223":{"id":"cli-15","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"**Prompts fail loudly without stdin.** If stdin closes before a prompt is answered (piped input, CI), the command exits **1** with `stdin closed before input was received — pass the value via its flag or environment variable instead`. In non-interactive contexts, supply every needed value via its flag or env var."},"224":{"id":"cli-16","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"Variable"},"225":{"id":"cli-17","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"Used by"},"226":{"id":"cli-18","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`SHADE_FROM_SECRET`"},"227":{"id":"cli-19","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`send` (sender secret)"},"228":{"id":"cli-20","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`SHADE_FEE_PAYER`"},"229":{"id":"cli-21","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`claim`, `withdraw` (fee-payer secret)"},"230":{"id":"cli-22","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`SHADE_FUNDING_SECRET`"},"231":{"id":"cli-23","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`claim`, `withdraw` (funding-account secret; signs the credit-gated relayer challenge)"},"232":{"id":"cli-24","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`SHADE_KEYSTORE`"},"233":{"id":"cli-25","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"every command (keystore path)"},"234":{"id":"cli-26","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"**Keystore path** resolves as: `--keystore <path>` → `$SHADE_KEYSTORE` → `~/.shade-keys.json`."},"235":{"id":"cli-27","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"**Relayers.** `--relay` (on `claim` and `withdraw`) is **repeatable and comma-separated**: `--relay https://a,https://b` and `--relay https://a --relay https://b&#x60; both work. It falls back to the comma-separated &#x2A;*`SHADE_RELAYERS`** env var when omitted. With more than one URL the client health-probes all candidates in parallel, routes to a healthy one (random by default, spreading users across the set), and fails over on relayer faults. `--verbose` prints the chosen relayer. When none is usable, the error lists every candidate with its rejection reason. See Relayer → Choosing a relayer."},"236":{"id":"cli-28","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"**Indexer.** `--indexer <url>` (on `scan` and `balance`) points account-method discovery at an announcement indexe&#x72; and falls back to the &#x2A;*`SHADE_INDEXER`** env var when omitted (flag wins; a single URL, no list). Horizon remains the source of truth: the scan verifies the indexer's health first, always finishes with a Horizon tail, and degrades silently to the plain Horizon walk on any indexer fault. `scan --verbose` reports the indexer in use."},"237":{"id":"cli-29","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"**Networks:** `--network testnet` is the default and the **only** accepted value today. Anything else, notably the removed `local` and the not-yet-audited `mainnet`, is rejected with an error. Mainnet (\"public\") arrives after the external audit."},"238":{"id":"cli-30","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Generate or recover stealth keys and write a keystore. Prints your meta-address."},"239":{"id":"cli-31","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Flag"},"240":{"id":"cli-32","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Description"},"241":{"id":"cli-33","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--keystore <path>`"},"242":{"id":"cli-34","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Keystore file path (defaults to `$SHADE_KEYSTORE` or `~/.shade-keys.json`)"},"243":{"id":"cli-35","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--password [password]`"},"244":{"id":"cli-36","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Encrypt the keystore with AES-256-GCM (prompts on stderr if the flag is given without a value)"},"245":{"id":"cli-37","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--plaintext`"},"246":{"id":"cli-38","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Write an **UNENCRYPTED** keystore (opt out of default encryption)"},"247":{"id":"cli-39","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--no-encrypt`"},"248":{"id":"cli-40","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Alias for `--plaintext`"},"249":{"id":"cli-41","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--mnemonic`"},"250":{"id":"cli-42","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Generate keys from a new BIP-39 mnemonic (enables recovery)"},"251":{"id":"cli-43","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--recover`"},"252":{"id":"cli-44","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Recover keys from an existing 12-word mnemonic"},"253":{"id":"cli-45","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--from-stellar-secret [secret]`"},"254":{"id":"cli-46","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Derive keys deterministically from a Stellar secret (SEP-53)"},"255":{"id":"cli-47","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--app-id <id>`"},"256":{"id":"cli-48","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Application id to scope derived keys (default: `default`)"},"257":{"id":"cli-49","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--key-scope <scope>`"},"258":{"id":"cli-50","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Key-derivation scope (default: `stealth`)"},"259":{"id":"cli-51","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--force`"},"260":{"id":"cli-52","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Overwrite an existing keystore (**destroys** the old keys and access to their unclaimed funds)"},"261":{"id":"cli-53","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"**Keygen refuses to overwrite.** If a keystore already exists at the target path, `keygen` exits with an error rather than clobbering it: overwriting destroys the old spend/view keys, and with them access to any unclaimed funds sent to the old meta-address. Either write elsewhere with `--keystore <path>`, re-display the existing meta-address with `shade address`, or pass `--force` if you really mean to overwrite."},"262":{"id":"cli-54","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"**Encryption is the default.** A plaintext keystore is written only when you explicitly opt out with `--plaintext` / `--no-encrypt`. Combining `--plaintext` with `--password` is an error, and an empty password is rejected."},"263":{"id":"cli-55","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-address","content":"Re-display the meta-address of an **existing** keystore. &#x2A;*No password needed:** both the plaintext and encrypted envelopes store the spend/view public keys in the clear, and the meta-address derives purely from them."},"264":{"id":"cli-56","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-address","content":"Flag"},"265":{"id":"cli-57","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-address","content":"Description"},"266":{"id":"cli-58","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-address","content":"`--keystore <path>`"},"267":{"id":"cli-59","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-address","content":"Keystore file path (defaults to `$SHADE_KEYSTORE` or `~/.shade-keys.json`)"},"268":{"id":"cli-60","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-address","content":"This is the safe answer to \"I lost my meta-address,\" as opposed to re-running `shade keygen`, which would overwrite the keys (and refuses to without `--force`)."},"269":{"id":"cli-61","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-send","content":"Send to a stealth address derived from a meta-address."},"270":{"id":"cli-62","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-send","content":"Argument"},"271":{"id":"cli-63","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-send","content":"Description"},"272":{"id":"cli-64","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-send","content":"`<meta-address>`"},"273":{"id":"cli-65","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-send","content":"Recipient meta-address (`shade:stellar:...` or `spend:view` hex)"