cryptography."],[131,"After the covered span, the scan **re-checks `/health` once more**: a gap the indexer recorded *while the scan was consuming its feed* discards the segment's results, and the tail re-walks the whole span, so a mid-scan hole can never advance the client cursor past a payment."],[985,"Against a credit-gated relayer (the default), `fundingAccount` alone is not enough: the relayer requires a fresh challenge **signed** by that account, so pass `fundingSigner` too (any `(message) => signature` function: a raw keypair, a wallet, an HSM). Both fields also apply to `withdraw()`'s `WithdrawOpts`."],[248,"Alias for `--plaintext`"],[841,"All arithmetic on **BigInt stroops**, never floats."],[144,"All configuration is environment variables. `packages/indexer/.env.example` is the annotated list:"],[88,"All entries are **persistent** storage. TTLs are extended on write and, notably, **on read**: `get_balance` and `get_nonce` bump a live entry's TTL back up to the ceiling. That means a passively-scanning recipient keeps their own balance alive without ever writing."],[1029,"All exported from `stellar-shade&#x60; so apps can branch cleanly. Every error extends a shared &#x2A;*`ShadeError`*&#x2A; base and carries a stable &#x2A;*`code`** string (e.g. `method_required`, `transaction_timeout`); branch on `e.code` when `instanceof` is unreliable across bundling/realm boundaries:"],[1095,"All six exported types work in **raw bytes** (`Uint8Array`), not hex strings:"],[921,"Allowed origin"],[183,"Allowed origin, permissive **on purpose** here, unlike the relayer: the candidate feed is public data anyone can read off Horizon"],[656,"Almost always the raw-scalar footgun: you built a keypair from `recoverStealthPrivateKey`'s output via `Keypair.fromRawEd25519Seed()` (or similar), which hashes it into a *different* key. &#x2A;*Sign with `signWithStealthKey`.** See Core Concepts."],[1014,"Also exported: `challengeMessage(endpoint, fundingAccount, nonce, amount, bind?)`, the canonical proof-of-control message, which must match the relayer byte-for-byte. See Relayer."],[1020,"Also exported: `normalizeRelayList(relay?)`, the canonical `string | string[]` → clean-list normalization (`[]`/whitespace → `undefined`)."],[477,"Amount deposited, in the token's smallest unit"],[275,"Amount in whole units (e.g. `100` for 100 XLM)"],[1043,"Amount isn't a positive finite number"],[375,"Amount to withdraw (default: full balance)"],[465,"An **announcement** is the on-chain record that lets you discover a payment. In the `pool` method it's a contract storage entry created **atomically with the deposit**: no deposit, no announcement, which makes announcement spam impossible. It carries:"],[631,"An account-method XLM send must be **strictly greater than 1 XLM**. Below that the new account can't meet its base reserve. Send more, or use `method: 'pool'`, which has no such floor."],[828,"An app sends the relayer a normal XLM payment."],[1155,"An indexer can *hide* payments (an availability failure) but cannot *fabricate* them: the client derives the stealth address from `R` itself and re-verifies on-chain at claim. It serves no address- or R-keyed queries, so the operator cannot link keys to requests; every scan ends with a Horizon tail and falls back to Horizon on any fault."],[1077,"An indexer endpoint responded non-2xx; carries `.status` and the indexer's own `.indexerCode`. The scan treats it as \"fall back to the Horizon walk\""],[130,"An indexer fault **mid-scan** degrades automatically to the Horizon walk from the last good cursor."],[1079,"An indexer was unreachable at the transport level (DNS/refused/timeout/invalid body); same Horizon fallback"],[413,"Announcement"],[306,"Announcement indexer URL for fast account-method discovery. Falls back to `$SHADE_INDEXER`; Horizon remains the source of truth"],[320,"Announcement indexer URL for fast account-method discovery. Falls back to `$SHADE_INDEXER`; Horizon remains the source of truth"],[509,"Any SAC token (XLM, USDC, …)"],[347,"App account to debit a credit-gated relayer fee against"],[383,"App account to debit a credit-gated relayer fee against"],[256,"Application id to scope derived keys (default: `default`)"],[780,"Apps and users can hand the SDK/CLI **several** relayer URLs instead of one (`ClientConfig.relayer: string[]`, CLI `--relay a,b` or the `SHADE_RELAYERS` env var). The client then health-probes every candidate in parallel and routes each relayed submission to a healthy one, failing over on relayer faults. See SDK Reference → RelayerPool for the exact health rule and failover semantics. A candidate counts as healthy only when its `/health` reports `status: 'ok'` on the right network with a workable balance, **and** its credit gate is passable by this caller. This is where the `store`/`sharedState` fields also let a client prefer a durable (`postgres`/`redis`) deployment over a dev-fallback one."],[1,"Architecture"],[481,"Architecture: how these concepts map onto components"],[753,"Architecture: the components and how data flows between them"],[569,"Architecture: the data flow behind each method"],[1203,"Architecture: where each control is implemented"],[270,"Argument"],[324,"Argument"],[360,"Argument"],[353,"Asset to claim, pool method: `native` or `CODE:ISSUER`"],[285,"Asset to send (default: native XLM, or `CODE:ISSUER`)"],[377,"Asset to withdraw (default: native XLM, or `CODE:ISSUER`)"],[53,"Atomic deposit + announcement. `sender.require_auth()`."],[7,"Authorization model"],[493,"Auto — Letting the client choose"],[851,"Backs"],[321,"Balances are aggregated per token in stroops and displayed with a readable asset label (`XLM` rather than the native SAC `C...` address)."],[545,"Base account reserve"],[533,"Because there is no view tag, **every hash-memo transaction on the network is a discovery candidate**. An unassisted scan walks the global Horizon transaction feed client-side, which makes a cold scan for a fresh recipient take minutes (and grow with the network). The fix is the **announcement indexer** (`packages/indexer`): a standalone service that walks the feed server-side **once for everyone**, keeps only hash-memo candidates with their operations, and serves them as a compact feed the client filters **locally**. It deliberately answers no address- or R-keyed queries, so the operator cannot link keys to requests. Point the SDK at one with `ClientConfig.indexerUrl`, or the CLI with `--indexer` / `SHADE_INDEXER`."],[818,"Body: `{ address, startingBalance?, fundingAccount, nonce, signature }` → `{ txHash, stealthAddress }`"],[801,"Body: `{ xdr, fundingAccount?, nonce?, signature?, authAmount? }` → `{ txHash, success: true }`"],[977,"Both are offline, with no network needed. `fromMnemonic()` generates a phrase when called with no argument and returns it alongside the keys for backup."],[143,"Both endpoints are rate limited per client IP: `429` with a `Retry-After` reporting the real remaining wait. The SDK treats a `429` as a fault (Horizon fallback), so the `/announcements` default is generous."],[792,"Build an unsigned sponsored-claim transaction"],[103,"Build the `deposit(...)` invocation, `prepareTransaction`, sign (local secret or external signer), submit"],[116,"Build the `withdraw(...)` invocation sourced by the **fee payer**"],[1004,"Build the sponsored claim tx (returns unsigned XDR)"],[115,"Build the withdraw message; sign it with `signWithStealthKey`"],[822,"Builds a relayer-sourced, **unsigned** transaction (60-second timebounds) with this exact operation sequence:"],[579,"Can I claim to a brand-new, empty address?"],[581,"Can I revoke a view key I shared?"],[576,"Can I send money directly to a meta-address?"],[903,"Cap on `/sponsor` starting balance"],[650,"Check `--network` matches where the payment was sent."],[1147,"Checks-effects-interactions: nonce and balance are committed before the external SAC `transfer`."],[494,"Choosing"],[759,"Choosing a relayer"],[322,"Claim a discovered payme